			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Stats on cleric hammer pet<BR>
HPS=250<BR>
MAX DAM=52<BR>
DEL 28<BR>
special note: You cannot cast any spell on this pet, you cannot give this pet anything and expect it to hold it like enchanter pets. You use to be able to cast DP on the pet and yes it would come back from death and actually be decent. As for a use for this pet, I have on several occassions used this pet to kill something with nothing but the pet and fear. It took roughly 15 minutes to kill 1 mob in sky but with constant fearing on the mob, the pet never lost a HP.<BR>
<BR>
Additional note, if you cast pet while your group is attacking a mob and while your pet is attacking that mob, you get hit by ANOTHER mob, the pet will immediately attack the next mob WITHOUT suiciding after the first mob is dead<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
It is theoretically possible to fear a mob constantly and let the pet do the damage. Long as mob is continually feared you shouldn't have a problem.<BR>
<BR>
Fand Fatehealer<BR>
lvl 56 Templar<BR>
Fennin Ro<BR>

