				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				*sigh* oh well I guess i'll try.<BR>
Clercs, by design, are ment for groups. They work best in groups, groups work best with them. So try to think of using this spell as a cleric, in a group fighting something realy hard and nasty. (for a single group that is, not in a 2+ group raid) One of the greatest things bout DoTs and pets, is you cast them, then can sit and med and do other things, unlike a nuke which just goes off (usualy generating alot of agro)<BR>
Now you're a cleric, in a group, deviding much of your time between medding and healing your group members. But lets say your group is lacking in damage output cabaility, and you'd like to contribute a little. Well that you pull out this little wonder, send it in, then sit down to med/heal as you normaly would.<BR>
In the longer battles higher lvls are more usedto having this can be quite a boon, as the pet will do much more damage over the course of the fight then the cleirc might have using the same amount of mana on nukes.<BR>
Same principle difrent situation, you're part of a cleric tank due and would like to contribute  more damage during the fight without generating alot of nasty agro on yourself which the single tank might find dificult to counter with taunts.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, just trying to show yahs there's no useless spells unless you don't take time to think of usesfor them :P
				</font>
